Package your LangGraph/LangChain object (the compiled graph, a Runnable, an AgentExecutor, etc.) as an MLflow model so it can be versioned, traced, loaded, and ultimately served (for example by a Databricks App or Model Serving). You do this with mlflow.langchain.log_model() / save_model() (the “LangChain flavor”)

Databricks’ Mosaic AI Agent Framework explicitly supports authoring with LangGraph and recommends using MLflow for tracing, packaging, and deployment—including deploying as a REST API via Databricks Apps.


