Databricks App templates (and the recommended AgentServer) are built to host MLflow-wrapped agents, giving you a REST /invocations endpoint with tracing baked in. Starting from a template like agent-openai-agents-sdk sets up a production-ready FastAPI server that calls your MLflow-wrapped agent under the hood. [learn.microsoft.com]
If you prefer to build the app yourself, you can still load the MLflow model in your FastAPI POST /invocations handler and forward requests to predict()—the result is the same pattern, just handcrafted. (The template saves you time and plugs neatly into Apps lifecycle commands.)

